{
  "texts": [
    "However, when the mass becomes large, the excitations are considered as the giant gravitons [49][50][51] which carry large angular momenta and behave as wrapped branes.",
    "In [27] we geometrically constructed the giant gravitons in the AdS 4 ETW brane region for the supergravity background involving asymptotic AdS 5 × S 5 regions, which we refer to as the ETW giant gravitons.",
    "They are the D3-branes wrapped on the 3-cycle as a fibration of S 2 (i), i = 1, 2 over the segment on Σ.",
    "We showed that they are the BPS configurations and their energy is bounded by the background 5-form flux associated with the 5-brane singularity.",
    "The construction can be generalized, as follows, to the orbifold ETW giant gravitons as the D3-branes wrapping the 3-cycle in the bagpipe geometries with the asymptotic AdS 5 × RP 5 regions by quotienting the ordinary ETW giant gravitons by the orbifold action (2.14)."
  ]
}